==English==
===Etymology===
Coined by [[w:Winston Churchill|Winston Churchill]] campaigning in the [[w:United Kingdom general election, 1906|1906 election]] (and repeated in the parliament in 1906).  He said that to describe certain (rather harsh) [[labour]] conditions in the [[Transvaal]] as [[slavery]] would be terminological inexactitude.  He meant only the literal sense of inaccurate terminology, but it was instead almost immediately taken to be a [[euphemism]] meaning an outright [[lie]].
===Noun===
'''[[terminological]] [[inexactitude]]'''
# {{euphemism}} A [[lie]] or [[falsehood]].